request.description:
### PATCH /auth/confirmEmail

This endpoint is used to confirm the user's email by providing the email and the one-time password (OTP).

#### Request Body

- `email` (string, required): The email address of the user.

- `otp` (string, required): The one-time password received by the user.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format and has the following schema:

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "message": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "data": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "_id": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "userName": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "email": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "gender": {
          "type": "string"
        },
        "address": {
          "type": "string"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

The response includes a `message` field and a `data` object with user details such as `_id`, `userName`, `email`, `gender`, and `address`.

